  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep10b_econ_threshold_2016",
    "description": "Economic threshold sweep in the 2016-block retarget regime \u2014 corrected rerun of sweep10.\nSweep10 accidentally ran with the CLI-default retarget=144 instead of 2016, making its results uninformative for the 2016-block research question.\nKey configuration changes vs sweep10:\n  - hashrate_split: 0.25 \u2192 0.50 (equal initial split, matching sweep9 which validated\n    the cascade mechanism and duration at this hashrate level)\n  - retarget_interval: 144 (accidental) \u2192 2016 (intended)\n  - duration: 13,000s (sweep9 showed retarget at t\u22488,106s + ~4,000s cascade = ~12,100s;\n    13,000s provides margin; validated sufficient by sweep9)\n\nCascade mechanism (from sweep9 at econ=0.70, hashrate=0.50):\n  - Both chains start 50/50 hashrate and mine at equal rate\n  - Economic_split drives a price differential (v27 price > v26 price at econ>0.50)\n  - Higher v27 price \u2192 v27 mining more profitable \u2192 pool drift toward v27 pre-retarget\n  - v27 accumulates hashrate advantage \u2192 mines 2016 blocks first at t\u22488,106s\n  - v27 retargets (difficulty drops ~50%); v26 hasn't hit 2016 blocks \u2192 stays at difficulty=1.0\n  - Post-retarget: v27 now far more profitable \u2192 remaining v26 hashrate forced to switch\n  - v26 never retargets \u2192 stuck at high difficulty \u2192 cascade completes\n\nResearch question: what is the minimum economic_split for v27 to win via the retarget mechanism?\n  - econ=0.82: v27 wins (confirmed sweep8)\n  - econ=0.70: v27 wins post-retarget (confirmed sweep9 at 50% hashrate)\n  - econ=0.60: uncertain \u2014 price gap is narrower; pool drift may be too slow\n  - econ=0.50: likely contested \u2014 symmetric economic signal gives no differential\n  - econ=0.35: v26 wins (economic majority on v26 side)\n\nIMPORTANT: Run with --retarget-interval 2016 and --duration 13000. Do NOT pass --enable-liveness-penalty (this is the baseline run with default oracle).\n",
